QUIP.DOC

Quip is a fortune cookie program that will present you with a
different wise saying (or wise crack) each time that you run it. 
You can display more than one quip by entering a number after the
quip command.

QUIP           Displays one quip.
QUIP 5         Displays five quips.


The quips themselves are stored in an ASCII text file QUIP.DAT
that can be edited manually or QUIPADD can be used to add quips. 
If the QUIP.DAT file is manually edited the index file QUIP.KEY
must be updated by running the program QUIPUPDT.  QUIPADD
automatically updates the index file.


File:          Description:
QUIP.C         Displays a random quip from QUIP.DAT
QUIPADD.C      Adds new quips to QUIP.DAT
QUIPUPDT.C     Updates QUIP.KEY after QUIP.DAT has been edited.
QUIP.DAT       A text file containing the quips.
QUIP.KEY       Index's the start of each quip in QUIP.DAT
QUIP.H         A C header file for the C programs.
QUIP.DOC       This file.
